    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_a4ecab90",
      "file_path": "pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 160,
      "message": "While those 2 artifacts are the same, but they have different tasks.\n\nThis is my understanding: \n\nThe maven-resources-plugin artifact in <profile> is responsible for copying resources, config file, .properties, ... to the docker image. \n\nThe maven-resources-plugin in the <build> is responsible for copying swagger files from src/main/resources to target/classes/META-INF/resources, during code build process.\n\nI noticed removing the artifact from <build> and keeping it in <profile>, swagger files are recreated in target/classes/META-INF/resources.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2399,
        "name": "Mohammadreza Pasandideh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "mohammadreza.pasandideh@amdocs.com",
        "username": "moreza"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-17 17:02:44.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_30dc56e4",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_04947fe0",
      "file_path": "pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 160,
      "message": "Yes, I agree.\n\nBut what would we like to archive here?  Would we just like to include swagger when we build the docker image or we would like include swagger in a normal build?\n\nPlus this is not how the other context builder does, I would prefer to keep all of the context builders the same way.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3479,
